# CSS Styling Conventions

## Linting

Enforced by **Stylelint** with `stylelint-config-standard` + Prettier integration.

```bash
npm run lint:css                   # Check
npm run lint:css -- --fix          # Auto-fix
```

Scoped to: `event-libs/v1/blocks/**/*.css` and `event-libs/v1/styles/*.css`

## File Organization

- **Block styles** — `event-libs/v1/blocks/<block-name>/<block-name>.css` (one per block)
- **Global styles** — `event-libs/styles/styles.css` (page-level base styles)
- **Lib styles** — `event-libs/v1/libs-styles.css` (shared block styles)

## Naming

- Use **kebab-case** for all class names
- Prefix block-scoped classes with the block name: `.event-agenda .agenda-container`
- Avoid generic class names that could collide across blocks

## Key Patterns

- No CSS-in-JS — all styles are vanilla CSS files
- No CSS preprocessors (no Sass/Less)
- No CSS modules — scoping is by block-name class convention
- Use CSS custom properties (variables) where provided by Milo
- Media queries for responsive behavior — no CSS framework

## Formatting

- 2-space indentation
- LF line endings
- Final newline required
